@node "intro" "Introduction to this door..."

INTRODUCTION

This is a little and nice wall!

Options :

* Up to 60 characters of text.
* Real name or anonymous

@endnode
@node "req" "Requirements..."

REQUIREMENTS

* Amiga ;-)
* Kickstart 2.04+ / Workbench 2.0+
* RexxMast running!
* Excelsior! v1.20+ (I think...maybe even below v1.20)

@endnode
@node "install" "Installation"

INSTALLATION

Put this door where ever you want it....

I have placed it in Doors:SimpleWall/
the datafile MUST be saved to Doors:
So add this line to your startup-sequence (or user-startup)

assign Doors: <BBSPATH:Doors>

e.g. assign Doors: BBS:Doors

You can put it in TEXT.WELCOME.USER.
The snapshot is called TEXT.WELCOME.USER1.IFF it is also in
the archive !

Or place it in the doors area.
Simply install it, it's an Arexx script, that should do it ;)

@endnode
